HEADWORD: Clamper
<hw>Clamp"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An instrument of
iron, with sharp prongs, attached to a boot or shoe to enable the wearer
to walk securely upon ice; a creeper.</def> <rj><au>Kane.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

